description: With the Islam holy month fast approaching, the CIA chief is in Qatar working to bring Hamas and Israel together on a pause in fighting that would see the release of hostages and deliveries of humanitarian aid
title: Burns again in Doha to push for cease-fire agreement before Ramadan

description: The U.N. report said Iran was responsible for the “physical violence” that led to Mahsa Amini’s death in detention. Amini’s death in 2022 sparked mass protests in Iran.
title: Iran is responsible for Mahsa Amini’s death in custody, U.N. report says

description: The growing stench in Port-au-Prince is a grisly new marker of Haiti’s violence and dysfunction.
title: Haitians shot dead in street and there’s no one to take the corpses away

description: Even in quieter years, al-Aqsa is a Ramadan tinderbox. Clashes here have been a repeated flash point for war.
title: At Jerusalem’s al-Aqsa Mosque, Ramadan brings uncertainty and fear

description: A student has started a campaign to get tourists to stop the long-standing tradition of groping the famous Molly Malone statue in Dublin.
title: Tourists’ groping of Irish statue prompts ‘Leave Molly mAlone’ campaign

description: Worries over French cheeses have spread since a study warned they’re “on the verge of extinction.” But a future without brie is not yet in the cards.
title: Will brie and Camembert cheeses go extinct? Here’s what scientists say.

description: Climate change and expanding cities mean more wild animals are clashing with the urban environment. This hospital picks up the pieces.
title: Wild on the Seine: Animal hospital tackles Paris’s wildlife casualties

description: The president was previously optimistic Hamas and Israel could reach a deal before the Muslim holy month, which is expected to begin in the coming days.
title: Israel-Hamas cease-fire deal by Ramadan ‘looking tough,’ Biden says

description: Afghanistan is seeing a wave of video bloggers who thrive under the Taliban, a regime that smashed televisions the first time it came to power in the 1990s.
title: The Taliban once smashed TVs. Now it fosters YouTubers to promote its image.

description: Faced with tensions in the South China Sea, the Philippines is signing new security deals and courting military assistance from governments across the world.
title: Philippines strikes security deals as tensions rise with China at sea

description: A federal judge ruled in favor of the Biden administration’s ‘parole’ program for migrants from Venezuela, Nicaragua, Cuba and Haiti, a pathway for legal entry into the U.S.
title: U.S. judge rejects GOP lawsuit that tried to stop Biden from paroling in migrants

description: It will take weeks and about 1,000 U.S. troops to mobilize and build a sprawling temporary pier off the Gaza coast, the Pentagon said.
title: How the U.S. military will use a floating pier to deliver Gaza aid
